tip.text: This is like a hidden gems for coffee and dessert in central Jakarta. The place is small yet cozy and warm..

formattedAddress: RUMAH COKRO, Jl. HOS Cokroaminoto 42 A
location.address: RUMAH COKRO, Jl. HOS Cokroaminoto 42 A

tip.text: Love this place. Everything is so good here. From coffee, appetizers,Main course to desserts. One of my fave dining spot in Jakarta
The food is quite good. Service is not bad either. But I've had better Italian food elsewhere at similar price. I'd recommend its Crostini Platter though.. The ingredients are so fresh!
Authentic Indonesian food at reasonably priced. Great ambience and service too. Definitely will come back! Love this place!
Ordered Flat White and it was good!!! And you can opt for soy milk and decaf. It's got homey and cozy ambience although a bit too spacey for me
For those who are into healthy and organic food, this place is your temple. Reasonably priced too! Cozy ambience, very relaxing to hang out here. You can shop at its store next door
If you're into healthy food, this place might be right for you. But I think it's kinda overrated and overpriced.  They only take cash, do not accept any credit card/debit card
Cozy, homey and so refreshing. Good food at generous portion and plenty choices for healthy drinks. I would recommend it to anyone looking for relaxing spot for lunch
Its chicken teriyaki is so good!!!  Didn't think it will come up in deep fried though.. If it wasn't so good, I would have felt guilty over the fried chicken
Ordered the 8 layer burrito but it was under my expectation. Taste wise it's pretty bland although the filling was generous. Could have been better
Food is great but service is quite slow. They are overwhelmed with customers yet don't seem understaffed. The paddy field doesn't seem natural though but it's okay

formattedAddress: Jalan Raya Goa Gajah (Banjar Teges Peliatan - Ubud)

tip.text: Toge gorengnya enak!!!! 1 pStrongly recommended. Walaupun agak sedikit mahal dgn harga 14rb per porsi utk standar makanan ngemper

formattedAddress: Jln Jendral Soedirman No. 23 A (Bogor Permai)

tip.text: Came here for Thanksgiving dinner. A bit pricey of 180k per plate of roasted turkey. But it tastes so good!!!  Staffs were attentive as they didnt let my wine glass empty during the meal course
Its charcoal buns burger is delightful accompsnied with crispy wedges. Service is generally good although music is a bit too loud for coffee shop
Love their Nachos!! A bit greasy but taste so good!! Very good service too. Recommended place!
Very generous portion. Too big for one person actually unless you're very hungry. Better share several menu with others instead of overloaded with one by yourself.
Its sweet corn and egg yolk is the reason why I love this place! So good!!!

formattedAddress: Grand Indonesia Shopping Town, West Mall, 3A Floor (Jl. M. H. Thamrin No. 1)
location.address: Grand Indonesia Shopping Town, West Mall, 3A Floor

tip.text: The worst food from all Trip Advisor certified spots I've tried in Spain
Reasonably priced for lunch set €11.95 including starter, main course, drink, bread and desserts. Taste wise was relatively good,dessert was the best part
Good food, good service, good wine! Highly recommended!!
I was expecting the taste to be better for premium priced pastry. Service was quite good though despite some staffs seemed to busy by themselves
Reasonably priced for mediocre food quality (referring to its Paella). Its Boquerones en vinagre was pretty good though. Service could have been better
Salmon with Bilbaina soy sauce is too die for! So good! Staffs are good in English despite the service was kinda slow

formattedAddress: Av. de la Constitución 10, Local Bajo 1
location.address: Av. de la Constitución 10, Local Bajo 1

tip.text: Friendly service with affordable priced menu. Don't expect much with the ambience but its burger is good! Delicious!
Spot to enjoy lunch with the view of La Sagrada familia. Great meal with friendly service
Love its kebab! So thick and so full of meats! Very delicious.. I will come back again for its kebab!

formattedAddress: Calle de Roger de Llúria, 56, 08009 Barcelona
location.address: Calle de Roger de Llúria, 56, 08009 Barcelona

tip.text: A warm neighbourhood breakfast spot. Plenty choices of bread and pastry. Taste wise is not bad but love the ambience!
Good friendly service with nice ambience. Its churros with chocolate dipping is strongly recommended as well as its homemade gelato! Don't miss its Gastronomic souvenir!
The seafood is so good and fresh! Unfortunately it's a bit pricey for a place located in the market! €25 for a mixed seafood platter. But i definitely will come back again!
The queue is kinda crazy. Perhaps a bit easier at noon than in the evening. A bit crampy but the service was fast! Anything I order was good, thank goodness for the english menu!
The pastry is so good!! Fresh and warm. They will ask you whether you would like it to be warmed.
Ordered the non-pork ramen and it's a bit bland maybe because of its chicken stock. The half boiled egg was good though.. Ambience wise nicer than most ramen place in Jakarta. Feel authentic

formattedAddress: Sentral Senayan 1, Basement Floor #10BC (Jalan Asia Afrika No. 8)

tip.text: Plenty choice of beers and the could come in large size. They have Cheap Monday promo with all beers buy 1 get 1 free&50% for food. Happy hours on Tuesday onwards 4-8pm. The live music is so so though
Its windows have drawn me to this coffee shop. Cozy ambience with plenty choices of food and drinks. Reasonable price as well. Recommended if you happened around Braga. Love its french toast!
Very lovely ambience and decor. Place to have romantic dinner with your loved one. Food wise is good, not just another pretty place with mediocre food.

location.address: Jl. Ciniru I No.2, Kebayoran Baru
formattedAddress: Jl. Ciniru I No.2, Kebayoran Baru

tip.text: Croque Monsieur is the chef's recommendation sandiwch. The portion is generous as its priced at IDR95k. Good and fresh but not that good to have it reordered

formattedAddress: Plaza Senayan, 3rd Floor (Jln. Asia Afrika No. 8)

tip.text: I love its brown curry! And you could choose the spicy level to suit your preference. Enjoy the curry with garlic naan, taste so good!

tip.text: Cozy place to have coffee and ice cream. Baileys ice cream is tasty although at steep price to pay.

formattedAddress: Jl. Taman Kemang 1 No. 6, Kemang Selatan (Kemang Selatan)
location.address: Jl. Taman Kemang 1 No. 6, Kemang Selatan

tip.text: Tex-mex food at reasonable price. Its homemade tortilla is fresh although its guacamole could be better. Very friendly staffs too. Its indie vibe makes it homey and cozy place to chill
A small charming coffee shop serving coffee and traditional Indonesian food. Coffee is decent but they should serve more snacks to enjoy the coffee with
Food is a bit on the high side but the coffee is awesome! Its salad is also very fresh

formattedAddress: Lippo Mall Kemang, Unit UG-03 (Jalan Pangeran Antasari No. 36)

tip.text: The place is tiny and you might need to share table but the chicken rice and salad is good. It's hawker so don't expect much but the taste
I love the decor! Coffee is decent and lots of bread choices for breakfast although the taste is kinda so so
I came here everyday during my stay at Da Nang.wide choices of food at reasonable price and they taste great! Nice ambience and helpful staffs too
Located above a bookstore. That's already a plus in my dictionary. The food is fresh and presented in unique way
Dinner time is always crowded and you might need to be on waiting list but the food worths the hype
Silence is golden here. Its cozy and peaceful ambience is worth of every penny you spend on its tea
I love its white rose! It's so good!! Definitely a must try!
It has more than 50 variants of Indonesian coffee. Amazing right? Its rustic decor gives you the cozy vibes. I just wish it has more kinds of snacks to accompany the coffee
The portion is small but the taste is so good! I wouldn't complain about the size because to me the size is just right. My faves are butterscotch and baileys

formattedAddress: Pacific Place 4th Floor #63 (Jalan Jendral Sudirman Kavling 52-53)

tip.text: The salad is very fresh! Pasta and pizza are not bad although I have tasted elsewhere better
Nice ambience for coffee time. They also provide decaf coffee which is quite rare for non chained coffee shop
26km from Da Nang. Rode a motorbike for nearly 2 hours return trip but it was a million dollar view
